---
import Layout from "@/layouts/Layout.astro";
import Nav from "@/components/Nav.astro";
import Footer from "@/components/Footer.astro";

const navLinks = [
  { href: "/", label: "Flagship" },
  { href: "#drift", label: "Drift detection" },
  { href: "#personas", label: "Persona library" },
  { href: "#faq", label: "FAQ" },
];
const navCta = { href: "#demo", label: "See it probing →" };
---

<Layout variant="synthetic">
  <Nav variant="synthetic" links={navLinks} cta={navCta} />

  <header class="hero">
    <div class="wrap">
      <span class="eyebrow">For Head of AI, AI-ops, model governance</span>
      <h1>Catch model drift <em>between audits.</em> Not after.</h1>
      <p class="lead">
        Phidea runs a persona-tagged probe library against your live AI every hour. A vendor model update breaks your claims-triage bot on a Tuesday — you know by Wednesday morning, not the next quarterly review.
      </p>
      <div class="cta-row">
        <a href="#demo" class="btn btn-primary">See it probing →</a>
        <a href="/" class="btn btn-ghost">See the platform</a>
      </div>
      <div class="hero-meta">
        <span><strong>Model-agnostic</strong> · OpenAI, Anthropic, Bedrock, fine-tuned</span>
        <span><strong>30ms p50</strong> · 70ms p99 gateway overhead</span>
        <span><strong>400+ personas</strong> · real-book, not edge-case</span>
      </div>
    </div>
  </header>

  <section id="drift" style="padding: 88px 0;">
    <div class="wrap">
      <div class="section-head">
        <div class="section-eyebrow">Drift detection</div>
        <h2>Every prompt. Every response. Graded in real time.</h2>
        <p class="lead">
          Grounding score against your policy corpus. Hallucination classifier on every output. Price-accuracy checks that fail-closed against your pricing API. Sessions that breach policy route to human review. The rest log to the ledger.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section id="personas" style="padding: 88px 0; background: var(--soft); border-top: 1px solid var(--line); border-bottom: 1px solid var(--line);">
    <div class="wrap">
      <div class="section-head">
        <div class="section-eyebrow">Synthetic buyers</div>
        <h2>Real-book personas. Running every hour.</h2>
        <p class="lead">
          Not red-team edge cases. The book you actually write: young renters in Lyon, first-home buyers in Denver, BOP shoppers in Milan, widowed retirees on annuity. Bereavement probes, jailbreak probes, adverse-event probes. New personas ship as new LOBs go live.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section id="blocking" style="padding: 88px 0;">
    <div class="wrap">
      <div class="section-head">
        <div class="section-eyebrow">Policy gate, optional</div>
        <h2>Block a bad answer before a customer sees it.</h2>
        <p class="lead">
          Phidea can sit as a policy gate in front of your agent. A flagged response is withheld, the user is served a safe fallback, the incident is logged with the full trace. Most carriers start in observe-only and turn blocking on after 30 days of clean traces.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section id="faq" style="padding: 88px 0; background: var(--soft); border-top: 1px solid var(--line); border-bottom: 1px solid var(--line);">
    <div class="wrap">
      <div class="section-head">
        <div class="section-eyebrow">FAQ</div>
        <h2>Straight answers.</h2>
      </div>
      <details>
        <summary>Does it slow the agent down?</summary>
        <p>Gateway adds ~30ms p50, ~70ms p99. Ledger writes are async. Nothing blocks the response path.</p>
      </details>
      <details>
        <summary>What models are supported?</summary>
        <p>OpenAI, Anthropic, Google, Cohere, Mistral, Azure, Bedrock, self-hosted, fine-tuned. Model-agnostic — if you can call it, we can observe it.</p>
      </details>
      <details>
        <summary>How is this different from standard red-teaming?</summary>
        <p>Red-teaming is episodic and adversarial. Phidea is continuous and behavioral. Real-book personas, every hour. Drift caught between vendor updates, not after a customer complaint.</p>
      </details>
      <details>
        <summary>Can the ledger sit on our infrastructure?</summary>
        <p>Yes. Container bundle. Same code path on managed SaaS, VPC, or air-gapped.</p>
      </details>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section id="demo" style="padding: 88px 0;">
    <div class="wrap">
      <div class="cta-panel" style="text-align: center; max-width: 720px; margin: 0 auto;">
        <h2>See it probing a real agent.</h2>
        <p>Fifteen-minute demo. We point the synthetic buyers at a public AI agent and walk through the traces, the drift alerts, and the ledger output.</p>
        <form action="https://phidea-forms.vercel.app/api/lead" method="POST" style="max-width: 480px; margin: 0 auto; display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 12px;">
          <input type="hidden" name="variant" value="synthetic" />
          <input type="email" name="email" placeholder="Your email" required style="padding: 14px 16px; border: 1px solid var(--line); border-radius: 10px; font-size: 15px;" />
          <input type="text" name="carrier" placeholder="Carrier name" required style="padding: 14px 16px; border: 1px solid var(--line); border-radius: 10px; font-size: 15px;" />
          <button type="submit" class="btn btn-primary" style="align-self: center;">See it probing →</button>
        </form>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <Footer />
</Layout>
